*DESCRIPTION_START
The antiseptic white walls of this corridor contrast almost painfully with its
black and silver marbled tiled floor. Four dark stained wooden doors, each with
a brass number plate, line the wall opposite an elevator.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
There is a brass number plate on the door that reads "401".
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
There is a brass number plate on the door that reads "402".
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB OPEN 2
   IFITEM 2 CLOSED
      AFFECT ITEMVAL2
      IFVAR PLRSINROOM ! 0
         CLEARVERB
         ECHO PLAYER It is locked.
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 3
There is a brass number plate on the door that reads "403".
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 4
There is a brass number plate on the door that reads "404".
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB EXAM 5
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR AZHFLOORNUM ! RNUM
      ECHO PLAYER The elevator is closed. You notice a glowing button on the wall beside it.
   ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER The elevator is open.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GO 5
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR AZHFLOORNUM ! RNUM
      ECHO PLAYER The elevator is closed. You notice a glowing button on the wall beside it.
   ELSE
      MOVEGROUP 1909
      ECHO OTHGROUP %P enters the elevator.
      AFFECT 1909
      ECHO OTHGROUP %P arrives.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFVERB PUSH 6
   IFVAR AZHFLOORNUM ! RNUM
      EQUAL AZHELEBUT4 1
   ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER You notice that the elevator is open.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
