*DESCRIPTION_START
The main theme of this room seems to be fun and relaxation, from soft leather
sofas placed in a seemingly random arrangement to the large fluffy cushions
strewn about the floor. A regulation dart board hangs on one of the walls while
rules for various Cafe games are on display for you to read.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFENTRY -1
   IFITEM 4
      ECHO PLAYER A Virtual Cafe game is currently being hosted in this room. Read the Rules
      ECHO PLAYER to find out which game and how it is played.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB EXAM 0
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR INTNUM3 = 1
      ECHO PLAYER The Rules item is used to display the rules for the Virtual Cafe games.
      ECHO PLAYER Simply TURN the rules until they display for the right game.
   ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER Why don't you try reading them?
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB TURN 0
   IFVAR INTNUM3 = 1
      CLEARVERB
      ADD ITEMVAL1 1
      IFNOITEM 4
         NEWITEM 4 447
      ENDIF
      IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 1
         ECHO PLAYER Set to display Trivia Rules.
      ENDIF
      IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 2
         ECHO PLAYER Set to display Jabberwocky Rules.
      ENDIF
      IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 3
         ECHO PLAYER Set to display Babble Rules.
      ENDIF
      IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 4
         ECHO PLAYER We don't need no stinkin' rulez!
         EQUAL ITEMVAL1 0
         REMOVEITEM 4
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB READ 0
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 0
      ECHO PLAYER There is currently no Virtual Cafe game being hosted here. For a listing of
      ECHO PLAYER Games and other Events, check the Virtual Cafe Calendar.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You read the rules...%c
      ECHO PLAYER    -------------------------------------------------------------------------
      ECHO PLAYER     VC Trivia by Azurian Skye      (c) 1995 Inner Circle Technologies, Inc.
      ECHO PLAYER    -------------------------------------------------------------------------%c
      ECHO PLAYER       Welcome to NovaLink's Virtual Cafe Trivia! Each round a question is
      ECHO PLAYER       displayed for you to read. You then have between 30 & 90 seconds to
      ECHO PLAYER       WHISPER your answer to the Game Host. You are then informed whether
      ECHO PLAYER       or not your answer was correct. The Game Host determines the length
      ECHO PLAYER       of time you are allowed to answer a question.%c
      ECHO PLAYER       Scores each round are based on the total number of answers received
      ECHO PLAYER       divided by the total number of CORRECT answers. So, if three out of
      ECHO PLAYER       six players are correct, each receives two points.%c
      ECHO PLAYER       Please, do NOT say your answer OUT LOUD. WHISPER your answer to the
      ECHO PLAYER       Game Host. That is the only way you can receive points. Also, don't
      ECHO PLAYER       cheat by whispering answers to a friend. It only ruins the game for
      ECHO PLAYER       the others playing.%c
      ECHO PLAYER    -------------------------------------------------------------------------
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 2
      ECHO PLAYER You read the rules...%c
      ECHO PLAYER    -------------------------------------------------------------------------
      ECHO PLAYER      Jabberwocky by Azurian Skye   (c) 1995 Inner Circle Technologies, Inc.
      ECHO PLAYER    -------------------------------------------------------------------------%c
      ECHO PLAYER      Welcome to Jabberwocky, a cryptogram puzzle game. Players are shown a
      ECHO PLAYER      phrase that has been encrypted by changing the order of its alphabet.
      ECHO PLAYER      For example, all its A's are turned into Z's. Players then take turns
      ECHO PLAYER      switching two letters at a time until the phrase has been deciphered.%c
      ECHO PLAYER      Once you know what the phrase is, simply WHISPER it to the Game Host.
      ECHO PLAYER      But be careful. A CORRECT ANSWER is worth TWICE the number of letters
      ECHO PLAYER      left encrypted in the phrase... but EACH INCORRECT ANSWER costs you 5
      ECHO PLAYER      points! And remember, SPELLING DOES COUNT!%c
      ECHO PLAYER                       To play Jabberwocky, type: PLAY GAME
      ECHO PLAYER                       To quit Jabberwocky, type: WAVE GAME%c
      ECHO PLAYER    -------------------------------------------------------------------------
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 3
      ECHO PLAYER You read the rules...%c
      ECHO PLAYER    ------------------------------------------------------------------------
      ECHO PLAYER     VC Babble by Azurian Skye     (c) 1995 Inner Circle Technologies, Inc.
      ECHO PLAYER    ------------------------------------------------------------------------%c
      ECHO PLAYER     Welcome to Babble -- A game of Silly Stories and Improvisation for the
      ECHO PLAYER     Virtual Cafe. Players take turns supplying words to fill-in-the-blanks
      ECHO PLAYER     of a story. When it's your turn, you'll be asked to provide a specific
      ECHO PLAYER     type of word (verb, noun, adjective). Once you've decided on the word,
      ECHO PLAYER     simply say it OUT LOUD (you CAN whisper it to the Game Host, but it is
      ECHO PLAYER     a lot more fun to just say it out loud). Once all the blanks have been
      ECHO PLAYER     filled, the story is displayed for all to see. There are no points. No
      ECHO PLAYER     winners. No glory. It's all just for fun!%c
      ECHO PLAYER                         To play Babble, type: PLAY GAME
      ECHO PLAYER                         To Quit Babble, type: WAVE GAME%c
      ECHO PLAYER     NOTICE: It will be easier to play Babble if you type 'SET PROMPT NONE'%c
      ECHO PLAYER    ------------------------------------------------------------------------
   ENDIF
ENDIF

