*DESCRIPTION_START
The ladies' restroom has been elegantly furnished, from the gold-trimmed mirror
to the gold sink fixtures. A pair of short leather padded stools rest in front
of an oak vanity counter where you can sit and refreshen your make-up. A row of
toilet stalls line one wall while a vending machine stands in corner beside a
round trash bin.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
Across the front of the trash bin are the words "Please don't litter".
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
There's really not that much to be seen. The stalls are the main function
points of this room. However, you do notice something strange; there is a pad-
lock on the middle stall.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB GO 1
   AFFECT 1931
   IFVAR PLRSINROOM = 0
      EQUAL FLAG2 1
   ENDIF
   AFFECT 1932
   IFVAR PLRSINROOM = 0
      EQUAL FLAG2 2
   ENDIF
   AFFECT 1930
   IFVAR FLAG2 = 0
      ECHO PLAYER You attempt to enter the left and right toilet stalls, but find that they
      ECHO PLAYER are both occupied. You're puzzled as to why the middle stall is padlocked.
      ECHO OTHERS %n attempts to enter one of the toilet stalls, but finds them all occupied.
      AFFECT 1931
      ECHO ALL You hear someone jiggling the door, trying to get in. You better finish up your business soon.
      AFFECT 1932
      ECHO ALL You hear someone jiggling the door, trying to get in. You better finish up your business soon.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR FLAG2 = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You enter the toilet stall on the right.
      ECHO OTHERS %N enters the toilet stall on the right.
      MOVE 1931
   ENDIF
   IFVAR FLAG2 = 2
      ECHO PLAYER You enter the toilet stall on the left.
      ECHO OTHERS %N enters the toilet stall on the left.
      MOVE 1932
   ENDIF
   CLEARVERB
ENDIF

