;Restroom (Men)
NUMBER 1933
NAME Restroom
REGION 1
FIXED_LIGHT
INDOOR_FLOOR
CHANNEL 777

CALL 49

EXIT U 1902
EXIT O 1919

ITEM 0 612 ADJ1=265 ADJ2=1032 OPEN
ITEM 1 1039
ITEM 2 360 ADJ1=292 ADJ2=470
ITEM 3 424 ADJ1=244
ITEM 4 247
ITEM 5 470 ADJ1=87 ADJ2=806
ITEM 6 853 ADJ1=753

*DESCRIPTION_START
The gentlemen's restroom has been richly paneled in dark wood, from the row of
stalls to the counter surrounding a porcelain sink. A silver edged mirror takes
up most of one wall while a vending machine stands in a corner beside a round
trash bin.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
Across the front of the trash bin are the words "Please don't litter".
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
There's really not much to be seen. The stalls are paneled in the exact same
dark wood as the rest of the room. However, you notice something strange; there
is a padlock on the middle stall.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB GO 1
   AFFECT 1934
   IFVAR PLRSINROOM = 0
      EQUAL FLAG2 1
   ENDIF
   AFFECT 1935
   IFVAR PLRSINROOM = 0
      EQUAL FLAG2 2
   ENDIF
   AFFECT 1933
   IFVAR FLAG2 = 0
      ECHO PLAYER You attemp to enter the left and right toilet stalls, but find that they are
      ECHO PLAYER both occupied. You're puzzled as to why the middle stall is padlocked.
      ECHO OTHERS %n attempts to enter one of the toilet stalls, but finds them all occupied.
      AFFECT 1934
      ECHO ALL You hear someone jiggling the door, trying to get in. You better finish up your business soon.
      AFFECT 1935
      ECHO ALL You hear someone jiggling the door, trying to get in. You better finish up your business soon.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR FLAG2 = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You enter the toilet stall on the right.
      ECHO OTHERS %N enters the toilet stall on the right.
      MOVE 1934
   ENDIF
   IFVAR FLAG2 = 2
      ECHO PLAYER You enter the toilet stall on the left.
      ECHO OTHERS %N enters the toilet stall on the left.
      MOVE 1935
   ENDIF
   CLEARVERB
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LOOK 2
   ADD FLAG3 1
   IFVAR FLAG3 = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You admire your reflection in the mirror.
      ECHO OTHERS %n gazes into the mirror, and instantly falls in love.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR FLAG3 = 2
      ECHO PLAYER You notice you're in bad need of a shave.
      ECHO OTHERS %n gazes into the mirror, and realizes %s needs a shave.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR FLAG3 = 3
      ECHO PLAYER You're admiring your reflection in the mirror, when you gasp as you catch a
      ECHO PLAYER glimpse of something hideous peeping over the top of the middle toilet stall
      ECHO PLAYER door. But when you turn around and look, nothing is there.
      ECHO OTHERS %n gazes into the mirror, then gasps and turns around, facing the toilet stalls.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR FLAG3 = 4
      ECHO PLAYER You look into the mirror only to see the face of a stranger staring back!
      ECHO OTHERS %n gazes into the mirror, but seems not to recognize %iself.
      EQUAL FLAG3 0
   ENDIF
   CLEARVERB
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GO 3
   EQUAL FLAG1 100
   ECHO PLAYER You walk over to the porcelain sink and begin washing your hands.
   ECHO OTHERS %n walks over to the porcelain sink and begins washing %h hands.
   CLEARVERB
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 4
It's attached to the side of an automatic hand dryer.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB PUSH 4
   IFVAR FLAG1 ! 100
      ECHO PLAYER Why don't you try washing your hands first? That's what the sink is for.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 100
      ECHO PLAYER You push a button on the wall and warm air blows out, drying your hands.
      ECHO OTHERS %n pushes a button on the wall and warm air blows out, drying %s hands.
      EQUAL FLAG1 105
   ENDIF
   CLEARVERB
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 5
The counter has been richly paneled in dark wood, as is most of the restroom.
It surrounds a porcelain sink, and on the wall above it hangs a silver edged
mirror.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB GO 5
   ECHO PLAYER You hop up on the counter.
   ECHO OTHERS %n hops up on the counter.
   POSITION SIT
   CLEARVERB
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 6
This vending machine sells the following three items:

Licorice (telepathy)  $10.00
Bubblgum                1.00
Cigarettes              1.00
*DESCRIPTION_END

STOREITEM 1947 -1 1
STOREITEM 1948 -1 10
STOREITEM 1124 -1 1

IFPREVERB SIT -1
   IFVAR POSITION ! 1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER There really aren't that many places to sit in a restroom, other than inside
      ECHO PLAYER the stalls.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LAY -1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER In a restroom?
ENDIF

IFPREVERB KNEEL -1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER In a restroom?
ENDIF
