NUMBER 1940
NAME Virtual Cafe
REGION 1
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
CAFE
MOVEMENT_ASTRAL
CHANNEL 777

CALL 49

EXIT O 1947

ITEM 0 91
ITEM 1 86
ITEM 2 1799
ITEM 3 1571 ADJ1=294
PUT 3 1630 VAL5=9
ITEM 4 1594

*DESCRIPTION_START
This cozy pine paneled cafe with its slowly turning wide bladed brass ceiling
fans and dim, intimate lighting provides a quaint and romantic setting and a
peaceful getaway from the grueling chores of the day. Beautiful leaded stained
glass windows, their gem-like hues lit from behind, hang in front of each of
the several clear paned openings. Glowing red tinted chimney candles and vases
of fresh cut flowers have been placed atop the polished surfaces of each round
oak table along with the Cafe's menus.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFENTRY
   ECHO GROUP As you enter, the hostess shows you to your table.
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 2
You read the menu.

         Soups - $2.00       Salads - $3.00      Sandwiches - $5.00
         --------------      --------------      ------------------
         Chicken Soup        Chicken Salad       Chicken Sandwich
         Mushroom Soup       Spinach Salad       Fish Sandwich
         Vegetable Soup      Tuna Salad          Roast Beef Sandwich

         Entrees - $10.00                        Beverages - $2.00
         ---------------------------             -----------------
         Blue Plate Special                      White Wine
         Baked Chicken and Corn                  Red Wine
         Fried Seafood Plate                     Cold Beer
         Roast Beef and Baked Potato             Coffee

         We will also pack you a lovely PICNIC BASKET for only $20.

To place an order, simply say OUT LOUD the item you want EXACTLY as it appears
on the menu. And please only order one item at a time. The waitress will bring
you your food. Immediately take your food when she offers it to you. After you
have taken your food, its price is added to your tab.

*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB GET 5
   IFVAR FLAG1 ! 666
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER That is not your order.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 666
      ADD FLAG4 ITEMVAL1
      EQUAL ITEMVAL1 0
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GET -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = 1630
      IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 9
         NEWITEM -1 1630
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFSAY TAB
   IFVAR FLAG4 ! 0
      STRCVT 0 FLAG4
      ECHO PLAYER The waitress comes by and quietly informs you that you owe $%0.00 on your tab.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR FLAG4 = 0
      ECHO PLAYER The waitress comes by whispers in your ear, "Honey, you're all paid up."
   ENDIF
   ECHO OTHERS The waitress comes by and whispers something to %N.
ENDIF

IFSAY CHECK,_PLEASE
   IFVAR FLAG4 ! 0
      STRCVT 0 FLAG4
      ECHO PLAYER The waitress comes by and quietly informs you that you owe $%0.00 on your tab.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR FLAG4 = 0
      ECHO PLAYER The waitress comes by whispers in your ear, "Honey, you're all paid up."
   ENDIF
   ECHO OTHERS The waitress comes by and whispers something to %N.
ENDIF

IFSAY CHECK_PLEASE
   IFVAR FLAG4 ! 0
      STRCVT 0 FLAG4
      ECHO PLAYER The waitress comes by and quietly informs you that you owe $%0.00 on your tab.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR FLAG4 = 0
      ECHO PLAYER The waitress comes by whispers in your ear, "Honey, you're all paid up."
   ENDIF
   ECHO OTHERS The waitress comes by and whispers something to %N.
ENDIF

