;
;
;Camorra's Apartment
NUMBER 1959
NAME Camorra's Loft
CAFE
MOVEMENT_ASTRAL
CHANNEL 777
REGION 1
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT

CALL 49

ITEM 0 1677
PUT 0 1226 ADJ1=32 ADJ2=306
PUT 0 475 ADJ1=317 ADJ2=966
PUT 0 661
PUT 0 803
ITEM 1 201 ADJ1=1240
ITEM 2 1304 ADJ1=74 ADJ2=973
ITEM 3 362 ADJ1=239 ADJ2=1144
ITEM 4 91 ADJ1=396 ADJ2=1170
PUT 4 546 ADJ1=1226 ADJ2=351
PUT 4 546 ADJ1=1226 ADJ2=351
ITEM 5 358 ADJ1=78 ADJ2=77 OPEN
PUT 5 237 ADJ1=347 VAL2=100
ITEM 6 377 ADJ1=312
ITEM 7 84 ADJ1=1146
PUT 7 469 ADJ1=239 ADJ2=347 ADJ3=545
ITEM 8 193
ITEM 9 460 ADJ1=347 ADJ2=187
PUT 9 198 ADJ1=499 VAL2=100

*DESCRIPTION_START
This spacious loft offers a quiet refuge from the busy world below. Rose petal
and acanthus leaf patterns spread across a cream colored background while rich
oaken woodwork climbs to shoulder level, framing the tall picture window on the
western wall. Errant sunlight filters across a mahogany desk, the warm hues of
burnt orange and gold illuminating the exposed oaken beams of the gently sloped
ceiling. A low end table is situated within easy reach of a cream colored sofa.
A plush rug warms the oak flooring before a simple stone fireplace. Sheltered
among slowly encroaching shadows is a four poster bed, draped with a luxurious
white satin comforter and scattered with pillows. From a darkened corner of the
loft, tendrils of steam and mist float and rise through some lush ferns.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The dark oak flooring has been polished to a lustrous shine.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
The finely crafted desk is stained a deep mahogany.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB SEARCH 1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER Your eyes are drawn to a half hidden sheet of parchment. Slowly you read:%c
   ECHO PLAYER            Gather out of Star dust,
   ECHO PLAYER                  Earth dust
   ECHO PLAYER                  Cloud dust
   ECHO PLAYER            And splinters of hail,
   ECHO PLAYER           One handful of dream dust
   ECHO PLAYER                 Not for sale.
   ECHO OTHERS %N looks through the paperwork on the desk.
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
The overstuffed sofa rests across from the fireplace, the cream colored
leather worn and comfortable.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 3
The plush bearskin rug is spread across the floor in front of the fireplace,
warming the varnished oaken floor.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB TOUCH 3
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You run your hand along the soft fur of the rug.
   ECHO OTHERS %N runs %h hand along the soft fur of the rug.
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 4
The end table has been set with an elegant cut crystal decanter and two
long-stemmed wine glasses.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 5
It is filled with white wine.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 6
The stone fireplace is set against the far wall, providing warmth and comfort
for cool nights. A supply of logs have been carefully stacked on the hearth.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB LIGHT 6
   IFVAR ITEMVAL1 ! 1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You kneel before the fireplace, carefully striking a long wooden match. As
      ECHO PLAYER the fire catches, the warmth begins to flow through the room. Tiny flames seem
      ECHO PLAYER to dance among the logs, bathing the shadows in a soft glow.
      ECHO OTHERS %N knees before the fireplace, carefully striking a long wooden match. As the fire catches, the warmth begins to flow through the room. Tiny flames seem to dance among the logs, bathing the shadows in a soft glow.
      POSITION KNEEL
      EQUAL ITEMVAL1 1
   ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER There's already a roaring fire in the fireplace.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB UNLIGHT 6
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER Once the fire is going, you just have to let it die out.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB POKE 6
   IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You stir the dying embers of the fire with the brass poker. The embers
      ECHO PLAYER flare up for a moment then slowly dim once again.
      ECHO OTHERS %N stirs the dying embers of the fire with the brass poker. The embers flare up for a moment then slowly dim once again.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB PUSH 6
   IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You add another log to the fire, sending a stream of sparks flying up the
      ECHO PLAYER chimney accompanied by a murmured crackle and hiss as the new log settles and
      ECHO PLAYER begins to burn.
      ECHO OTHERS %N adds another log to the fire, sending a stream of sparks flying up the chimney accompanied by a murmured crackle and hiss as the new log settles and begins to burn.
    ENDIF
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 7
The four poster bed has been crafted from dark oak, climbing vines intricately
carved within the tall posts.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB GO 7
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You lay down on the bed, running your hands over the sheets.
   ECHO OTHERS %N lays down on the bed, running %h hands over the sheets.
   POSITION LAY
   EQUAL FLAG1 2
ENDIF

IFPREVERB PULL 7
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You turn down the plush comforter on the bed, revealing ivory satin sheets
   ECHO PLAYER that look cool and inviting.
   ECHO OTHERS %N turns down the plush comforter on the bed, revealing ivory sheets that look cool and inviting.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB TOAST -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = 546
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You hurl the wine glass into the stone fireplace, the shards shattering
      ECHO PLAYER against the flames.
      ECHO OTHERS %N hurls the wine glass into the stone fireplace, the shards shattering against the stones.
      REMOVEITEM -1
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LOOK -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = 1226
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER Within a recessed alcove, soft shadows and lush ferns barely conceal a brass
      ECHO PLAYER spiral staircase, the steps carved of pale white marble and worn soft from the
      ECHO PLAYER passage of both time and feet.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = 475
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER The tall picture window runs the length of the western wall, providing a
      ECHO PLAYER breathtaking view of the horizon at sunset.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = 661
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You notice tendrils of steam and mist floating through the lush ferns in
      ECHO PLAYER one corner of the loft, while another group of ferns almost seem to try to
      ECHO PLAYER hide a shadowy alcove.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = 803
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER The alcove is partially hidden by the ferns and totally cloaked in shadows.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GAZE -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = 475
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER Off in the distance you can see a small pond surrounded by trees.
      ECHO OTHERS %N stands quietly at the window, seemingly lost in thought.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB SNIFF -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = -1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER The gentle ocean breeze carries the haunting scent of night jasmine through
      ECHO PLAYER the open windows.
      ECHO OTHERS %N catches the scent on the breeze.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LISTEN -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = -1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER The quiet of the room is almost tranquil, whispers of outdoor life combining
      ECHO PLAYER with the muted voices and familiar sounds of the house.
      ECHO OTHERS %N pauses for a moment, listening.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB SEARCH -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = -1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER Within a recessed alcove, soft shadows and lush ferns conceal the brass
      ECHO PLAYER spiral stairway.
      ECHO OTHERS %N reaches out, touching the lush ferns.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LAY -1
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR POSITION = 0
      EQUAL FLAG1 1
      ECHO PLAYER You stretch out in front of the fireplace on the plush bearskin rug.
      ECHO OTHERS %N stretches out in front of the fireplace on the plush bearskin rug.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION = 1
      IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
         ECHO PLAYER You stretch out on the sofa, sinking into the soft leather.
         ECHO OTHERS %N stretches out on the sofa, sinking into the soft leather.
      ENDIF
      IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
         ECHO PLAYER You lay back on the plush bearskin rug.
         ECHO OTHERS %N lays back on the plush bearskin rug.
      ENDIF
      IFVAR FLAG1 = 2
         ECHO PLAYER You lay back in bed.
         ECHO OTHERS %N lays back in bed.
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION = 2
      ECHO PLAYER You are already laying down.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION = 3
      ECHO PLAYER You lay back on the plush bearskin rug.
      ECHO OTHERS %n lays back on the plush bearskin rug.
   ENDIF
   POSITION LAY
ENDIF

IFPREVERB SIT -1
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR POSITION = 0
      EQUAL FLAG1 1
      ECHO PLAYER You sit down on the plush bearskin rug.
      ECHO OTHERS %N sits down on the plush bearskin rug.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You are already sitting.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION = 2
      IFVAR FLAG1 = 2
         ECHO PLAYER You sit up in bed.
         ECHO OTHERS %N sits up in bed.
      ELSE
         ECHO PLAYER You sit up.
         ECHO OTHERS %n sits up.
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION = 3
      ECHO PLAYER You sit down on the plush bearskin rug.
      ECHO OTHERS %N sits down on the plush bearskin rug.
      EQUAL FLAG1 1
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB STAND -1
   IFVAR POSITION = 2
      IFVAR FLAG1 = 2
         CLEARVERB
         ECHO PLAYER You roll out of bed onto your feet.
         ECHO OTHERS %N rolls out of bed onto %h feet.'
         POSITION STAND
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
   EQUAL FLAG1 0
ENDIF

IFPREVERB KNEEL -1
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 2
      ECHO PLAYER You roll out of bed and kneel down on the bearskin rug.
      ECHO OTHERS %N rolls out of bed and kneels down on the bearskin rug.
   ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER You kneel down on the bearskin rug.
      ECHO OTHERS %N kneels down on the bearskin rug.
   ENDIF
   POSITION KNEEL
   EQUAL FLAG1 1
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GO -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = 1226
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO OTHERS The ferns rustle as %P disappears into the shadows of the alcove.
      ECHO PLAYER The ferns rustle as you step into the shadows of the alcove and climb down
      ECHO PLAYER the brass spiral stairway.
      MOVEGROUP 1958
      AFFECT 1958
      ECHO OTHGROUP %P steps out of the shadows of the alcove.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = 803
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You notice a brass spiral stairway recessed inside the alcove.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB CLIMB -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = 1226
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO OTHERS The ferns rustle as %P disappears into the shadows of the alcove.
      ECHO PLAYER The ferns rustle as you step into the shadows of the alcove and climb down
      ECHO PLAYER the brass spiral stairway.
      MOVEGROUP 1958
      AFFECT 1958
      ECHO OTHGROUP %P steps out of the shadows of the alcove.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

;
;
;ELIZA'S FLOWER SHOPPE
NUMBER 1960
NAME Eliza's Flower Shoppe
CAFE
MOVEMENT_ASTRAL
CHANNEL 777
REGION 1
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT

CALL 49

EXIT O 1950

ITEM 0 475
ITEM 1 195
ITEM 2 381
ITEM 3 1308
EXTEND 3 of a distinguished looking man
ITEM 4 448
EXTEND 4 of colored glass marbles
ITEM 5 1571 ADJ1=77
ITEM 6 86 ADJ1=451
ITEM 7 470 ADJ1=216
ITEM 8 1592
PUT 8 1046 VAL2=4
ITEM 9 204

*DESCRIPTION_START
The cheerful little flower shop is well lit and furnished. Over in one corner,
you notice a small fireplace with a big chair set in front of it. Hanging above
an oak counter is a sign displaying the wares of the shop. Looking around, you
see the usual flowers and gardening supplies.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFENTRY -1
   ECHO GROUP Eliza looks up from behind the counter at you and smiles warmly.
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
Looking out the window you see the outside of the shop. From here you have a
perfect view of the Weeping Willow Tree and Eliza's store front garden. Off in
the distance, you can barely make out the crystal blue pond.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
You see a quaint looking stone fireplace. You notice a mantle cluttered with
assorted treasures belonging to Eliza.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
Sitting on the mantle are a bowl of colored glass marbles and a crystal vase,
mementos from an age gone by. Hanging above the center of the mantle you notice
a large portrait.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM ON 2
On the mantle you see a bowl of colored glass marbles and a cyrstal vase.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 3
You see a mature man with silver hair and deep blue eyes. He is wearing a
formal blue suit and his eyes seem to glint with some kind of secret. On the
frame of the portrait you see a gold plate reading the name, "Henry" in
flowing script.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 4
The bowl is descorated with the same delicate floral design that apears on
the other pieces of china in the room. You notice the marbles in the bowl are
very colorful and have swirling patterns.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM IN 4
In the bowl you see a rainbow of colored glass marbles.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB OPEN 4
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You start to open the bowl of colored glass marbles, but Eliza swats your
   ECHO PLAYER hand away.
   ECHO OTHERS %N starts to open the bowl of colored glass marbles, but Eliza swats %h hand away.
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 5
The hand cut crystal vase is carved with an intricate floral design. The vase
holds fresh cut roses straight from Eliza's garden.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM IN 5
In the crystal vase you see a bouquet of fresh cut roses.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 6
The old chair looks soft and comfortable. The once floral pattern has faded
into some pale swirls.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 7
The handsome oak counter looks as though it has recently been polished. On
top of the counter you notice a plate of chocolates.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM ON 7
On the oak counter you see a plate of chocolates.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB KICK 7
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR ROUNDTIME = 0
      ECHO PLAYER You kick an oak counter!
      ECHO OTHERS %N kicks an oak counter!
      EQUAL ROUNDTIME 5
      ADD FLAG1 1
      PLREVENT 1
      CONTPLREVENT
      IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
         ECHO PLAYER Eliza glares at you.
         ECHO OTHERS Eliza glares at %n.
      ENDIF
      IFVAR FLAG1 = 2
         ECHO PLAYER Eliza starts to swat at you with her feather duster.
         ECHO OTHERS Eliza swats at %N with her feather duster.
      ENDIF
      IFVAR FLAG1 = 3
         ECHO PLAYER This time, Eliza seems to forget herself and starts scolding you in a rapid cockney accent.
         ECHO OTHERS This time, Eliza seems to forget herlsef and starts scolding %N in a rapid cockney accent.
      ENDIF
      IFVAR FLAG1 = 4
         ECHO PLAYER Eliza runs you out of her flower shop!
         ECHO OTHERS Eliza runs %n out of her flower shop!
         DISBAND
         MOVE 1950
         SHOWROOM 1950
         AFFECT 1950
         ECHO OTHERS You hear someone yelling in a cockney accent, and seconds later %N is kicked out of the flower shop.
      ENDIF
   ELSE
      STRCVT 0 ROUNDTIME
      ECHO PLAYER [Wait %0 seconds...]
   ENDIF
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 8
The small plate is covered in a delicate floral design. Eliza notices you
gazing at the luscious chocolates on the plate and offers you to help yourself.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 9
The sign displays the wares of Eliza's Flower Shoppe.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 9
You read the sign...

                     Welcome to Eliza's Flower Shoppe

           Rose bouquet................................... $15.00
           Wildflower bouquet.............................   5.00
           Roses (red, yellow, pink and white)............   2.00
           Rosebuds (red, yellow, pink and white).........   1.00
           Violets........................................   3.00
           Lilacs (lavender and white)....................   3.00
           Orchids (white, purple, black and yellow.......   8.00

*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB LISTEN -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = -1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You hear Eliza softly humming to the music playing in the shop.
      ECHO OTHERS %N listens to %h surroundings.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB SMELL -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = -1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER The shop smells pleasantly of a combination of herbs and flowers.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GET -1
   IFCARRY 1046 -1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER Eliza frowns at you for being a pig. Why not eat the piece of chocolate you
      ECHO PLAYER already have before taking another?
   ELSE
      IFVAR ARCHNUM = 1046
         NEWPUT 8 1046 VAL2=4
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
ENDIF

